## Overview

Fixed critical scrolling bug where Dashboard page (and all pages) could not scroll beyond the initial viewport height. Users could not access widgets beyond the first 4 default widgets.

---

## Problem Statement

### User Report

> "Ever since implementing the change on the calendar / planning page to only be able to scroll inside that function instead of the entire page scrolling away the headers and titles, every other page now acts the same. This cannot be the case. It doesn't matter for Kanban and Notes since that all fits into one page, but adding a bunch of widgets to the dashboard I can no longer scroll past the default 4 widgets to see any of them. That scrolling function should only be applicable on the Planning page due to the Week/Day/List views inside the calendar."

### Root Cause Analysis

The issue was in the Layout component (`src/components/Layout.tsx`):

**Line 33-49 (BEFORE FIX):**
```tsx
<div className="flex-1 flex flex-col transition-all duration-200 overflow-hidden">
  <main className="flex-1 py-6 overflow-hidden">  {/* ❌ overflow-hidden prevents scrolling */}
    <div className="w-full h-full px-6">          {/* ❌ h-full locks height to parent */}
      {children}
    </div>
  </main>
</div>
```

**Chain of Fixed-Height Containers:**
1. App container: `h-screen` (fixed to viewport height)
2. Main content wrapper: `flex-1 overflow-hidden` (fills available space, no scroll)
3. Main tag: `flex-1 overflow-hidden` (fills parent, no scroll)
4. Content div: `h-full` (locks to parent height)

**Result:** All page content was locked to viewport height with no ability to scroll.

### Why This Happened

The Planning page needed internal scrolling (calendar grid scrolls while header stays fixed). The initial implementation used `overflow-hidden` on the main tag to prevent double scrollbars. However, this prevented ALL pages from scrolling, not just Planning.

---

## Solution

### Fix 1: Layout.tsx - Enable Main Tag Scrolling

**File:** `src/components/Layout.tsx`
**Lines:** 36, 46

**Changes:**
```tsx
// BEFORE
<main className="flex-1 py-6 overflow-hidden">
  <div className="w-full h-full px-6">
    {children}
  </div>
</main>

// AFTER
<main className="flex-1 py-6 overflow-y-auto">  {/* ✅ Allow vertical scrolling */}
  <div className="w-full px-6">                 {/* ✅ Removed h-full constraint */}
    {children}
  </div>
</main>
```

**Impact:**
- Dashboard: Can now scroll to see all widgets ✅
- Notes: Can scroll through long note lists ✅
- Tasks: Can scroll Kanban columns (if needed) ✅
- Settings: Can scroll long settings sections ✅
- Planning: Needs special handling (see Fix 2) ⚠️

---

### Fix 2: Planning.tsx - Use Calculated Height

**File:** `src/pages/Planning.tsx`
**Lines:** 25, 36

**Changes:**
```tsx
// BEFORE
<div className="planning-page h-full flex flex-col">        {/* ❌ h-full won't work without parent h-full */}
  <div className="flex-1 min-h-0">                         {/* ❌ flex-1 can't calculate without parent */}
    <Calendar />
  </div>
</div>

// AFTER
<div className="planning-page">                            {/* ✅ Normal document flow */}
  <div className="h-[calc(100vh-220px)]">                  {/* ✅ Fixed height for internal scrolling */}
    <Calendar />
  </div>
</div>
```

**Calculation Breakdown:**
- `100vh` = Full viewport height
- `-220px` = Header (60px) + Footer (40px) + Page title (60px) + Padding (60px)
- Result: Calendar gets ~800-900px height on typical screens

**Calendar Internal Scrolling (Unchanged):**
- Calendar.tsx line 334: `<div className="calendar-widget h-full flex flex-col">`
- Calendar.tsx line 407: `<div className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto px-4 pb-4">` ← This scrolls

